title: $:/plugins/crosseye/simple-outline/usage
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki

!! Create Outline

Once you've installed `simple-outline` to your TiddlyWiki 5.3.0+ wiki and saved, you can create an outline tiddler and use the widget:

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutlineTiddler}} class="outline"/>
```

Or supply the outline text inline:

```
<$simple-outline text="""
!! Section heading

  Group label
    + tiddler-name
    + display text :: tiddler-title
""" class="outline"/>
```

!! Input Format

Each line of the `text` attribute describes one node:

|!Syntax |!Meaning |
|`!! Heading` |Section header — renders as `<h2>` |
|`+ tiddler-name` |Tiddler reference — expands to show its body if it exists |
|`display text :: tiddler-name` |Same, with an explicit label instead of the tiddler title |
|Plain text |Structural group — collapsible if it has children |
|Indentation |Each extra indent level (leading spaces) is one nesting level deeper |

For tiddler references, the displayed label comes from the first non-empty value in the `label-fields` chain (default: `summary` → `caption`), falling back to the name as written in the outline.

!! Attributes

|!Attribute |!Default |!Purpose |
|`text` |— |The outline description (required) |
|`class` |`outline` |CSS class(es) added to the container `<div>` |
|`summary-template` |— |Tiddler rendered inside each `<summary>` for tiddler items; receives `currentTiddler` and `so-label` |
|`group-template` |— |Tiddler rendered inside each `<summary>` for group nodes; receives `so-label` only |
|`header-template` |— |Tiddler rendered inside `!!` section header divs, replacing the default `<h2>`; receives `so-label` only |
|`detail-template` |— |Tiddler rendered as the expanded body for each tiddler item; receives `currentTiddler` and `so-label` |
|`tiddler-link` |— |When non-empty, adds a link on the summary row that opens the tiddler without toggling the node |
|`tiddler-link-label` |`✳` |Glyph or text for the `tiddler-link` (only used when `tiddler-link` is set) |
|`open-depth` |`0` |Levels to open by default on first render (0 = all closed) |
|`label-fields` |`summary caption` |Space-separated field names tried in order to compute the display label |

!! CSS Hooks

The plugin generates a predictable DOM structure that you can target with CSS.

|!Selector |!Meaning |
|`.outline` (or your `class`) |The container `<div>` |
|`.level-0` … `.level-N` |Applied to every element; controls indentation |
|`.so-header` |`<div>` wrapping a `!!` section header |
|`.so-group` |`<details>` for a plain collapsible group node |
|`.so-tiddler` |`<details>` for a tiddler item that has body content |
|`.so-leaf` |`<div>` for a tiddler item with no body content |
|`.so-text` |`<div>` for a plain label line (no `+` prefix) |
|`.so-missing` |Added to `.so-leaf` when the referenced tiddler does not exist |
|`.outline details[open]` |A currently-expanded node |
|`.outline details > summary` |The clickable row header |
|`.so-arrow` |`<span>` inside `<summary>` holding the rotating arrow icon |
|`.so-label` |`<span>` wrapping the display text inside `<summary>` |
|`.so-toggle` |`<span>` after `.so-label` when `summary-template` is active — empty; useful for custom expand/collapse indicators |
|`.ltgraybox` |`<div>` wrapping expanded tiddler content |
|`.item` |Non-expandable tiddler reference (same element as `.so-leaf`; kept for compatibility) |
|`.outline h2` |Section header text |

To replace the default arrow with your own indicator:

```css
/* hide the default arrow */
.my-outline .so-arrow { display: none !important; }

/* use .so-toggle to show + / – instead */
.my-outline details > summary .so-toggle::before { content: "+"; }
.my-outline details[open] > summary .so-toggle::before { content: "−"; }
```

!! summary-template

When set, the named tiddler is rendered inside each `<summary>` element instead of plain text.  Two variables are available: `<<currentTiddler>>` (the item's tiddler title) and `<<so-label>>` (the pre-computed display label).

Example template tiddler:

```
<span class="so-label"><<so-label>></span><span class="so-toggle"></span>
```

Usage:

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} class="my-outline"
  summary-template="My Summary Template"/>
```

!! detail-template

When set, the named tiddler is rendered as the expanded content for each item instead of transcluding the tiddler's body directly.  The same two variables are available.

Example template tiddler — adds a linked title above the body:

```
<$link to=<<currentTiddler>> class="so-detail-title"><<currentTiddler>></$link>
<$transclude $tiddler=<<currentTiddler>> $mode="block"/>
```

CSS for the linked title:

```css
.outline .so-detail-title {
    display: block;
    font-weight: bold;
    border-bottom: 1px solid #aac;
    margin-bottom: 0.4em;
}
```

Usage:

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} class="outline"
  detail-template="My Detail Template"/>
```

!! open-depth

Pre-opens nodes by level on first render.  Nodes at levels 0 through `open-depth - 1` start open; deeper nodes start closed.  Once a user has toggled a node, their choice is saved and takes precedence.

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} open-depth="2"/>
```

With `open-depth="2"`, level-0 and level-1 nodes open automatically on the first visit.  Levels 2 and deeper stay closed until the user expands them.

!! label-fields

Controls which tiddler fields are consulted (in order) when computing the display label for a `+` item.  The first non-empty value wins; the text written in the outline is the final fallback.

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} label-fields="name caption"/>
```

The default is `"summary caption"`, which preserves the behaviour from earlier versions.  Supply a single field name to pin to one field, or a longer list to extend the fallback chain.

!! group-template

When set, the named tiddler is rendered inside the `<summary>` of each plain group node (collapsible labels that are not tiddler items).  One variable is available: `<<so-label>>` (the group text).  `<<currentTiddler>>` is not set — group nodes have no associated tiddler.

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} group-template="My Group Template"/>
```

!! header-template

When set, the named tiddler is rendered inside each `!!` section header div, replacing the default `<h2>`.  One variable is available: `<<so-label>>` (the header text).

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} header-template="My Header Template"/>
```

Example template — renders a styled `<h2>` with a custom class:

```
<h2 class="my-section-title"><<so-label>></h2>
```

!! tiddler-link

When non-empty, adds a small link element to the right of every tiddler item's label.  Clicking it opens the tiddler in the story river without toggling the outline node.

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} tiddler-link="yes"/>
```

The link sits inside `<summary>` at the trailing edge (pushed right by `margin-left: auto`).  A `stopPropagation` handler prevents the click from reaching the native toggle, so the node stays in its current open/closed state.  Use `tiddler-link-label` to change the glyph:

```
<$simple-outline text={{MyOutline}} tiddler-link="yes" tiddler-link-label="→"/>
```

Style the link with `.so-tiddler-link` in CSS.
